UH5 domestic structure: BB phase = phase IV of UH5: there is also undecorated pottery in this layer: The different stratigraphic relationships allow us to propose up to 4 construction episodes. The first is defined by a single space (UH5) with a trapezoidal floor plan and a surface area of around 25 m2 delimited by medium/large calibre masonry walls. This space is attached to the raised structure, which would place both of them in the earliest times of the settlement. Inside, a small masonry bench attached to one of the walls, a floor made of large stone slabs and rammed earth, and a combustion structure that was documented to be completely uncovered. In this level of use -dating from a wheat seed in ca. 2480-2280 cal BC; 3900±40BP- a set of archaeological materials was found, including the presence of a minimum of thirteen ceramic vessels with bell-shaped decoration which, due to their characteristics, were found to have been used in a number of different ways.
